r other large bowl and cover to keep warm while you prepare the chicken and masala sauce."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Masala sauce"},{"content":"Place onion, garlic, ginger and chilli into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add butter or ghee and sauté <b>3 min\/120°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add chopped tomatoes, tomato paste, salt, sugar, garam masala and 100 g of reserved tikki paste and cook <b>10 min\/100°C\/speed 1<b>."},{"content":"Add yoghurt and cream and blend <strong><b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>-8, increasing speed gradually<\/strong> <strong>from speed 4 to speed 8.<\/strong> Set sauce aside in mixing bowl to stay warm."},{"content":"Place a large non-stick, high-sided griddle or frying pan over a high heat and cook marinated chicken for 10 minutes, or until cooked through."},{"content":"Pour sauce into a serving bowl, then add chicken and stir to combine. Serve immediately on a bed of the saffron rice garnished with coriander leaves."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Serve Chicken tikka masala with Naan bread and condiments of choice.","Top up jars with a little more oil after each use so that the paste stays submerged. This will assist with preserving the paste. If kept covered in a sealable jar in the refrigerator this paste will last up to 4 weeks.","Use the tikka paste to make a vegetable, meat, prawn, fish or paneer tikka, or tikka masala curry. It is also wonderful as a marinade for chicken to be barbecued.","To try making your own garam masala, please refer to the recipe in <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i>."],"basicInfo":["easy","40m","4h 40m","6 portions"]}